This pattern is very common, so it is worth learning by example.

== Common beginner verbs

These are useful early separable verbs:

- `opstaan` -> get up
- `aankomen` -> arrive
- `weggaan` -> go away, leave
- `meenemen` -> take along
- `terugkomen` -> come back
- `opbellen` -> call

Try to learn them as full vocabulary items, not as loose pieces.

== One sentence, three patterns

Look at the same verb in three common patterns:

- present main clause: `Ik sta vroeg op.`
- with modal verb: `Ik wil vroeg opstaan.`
- perfect tense: `Ik ben vroeg opgestaan.`

That single comparison teaches most of what you need at the beginner level.

== A useful study habit

Pick one separable verb and practice it in these three forms:

- `Ik kom aan.`
- `Ik wil aankomen.`
- `Ik ben aangekomen.`

Then change the subject or the time expression:

- `Morgen komen wij aan.`
- `Wij willen vroeg aankomen.`
- `Wij zijn vroeg aangekomen.`

This helps the pattern become automatic.
